---

### 🎯 TL;DR

| Method | Behavior on `Err` | Use Case |
|--------|-------------------|----------|
| `.unwrap()` | Panics with "called `Result::unwrap()` on an `Err` value" | Quick prototyping |
| `.expect("msg")` | Panics with your custom message | Debugging & documentation |

---

### 🔍 Deep Dive — With EVA Energy! 💫

#### 🧱 Basic Example

```rust
fn main() {
    let result: Result<i32, &str> = Ok(42);

    // unwrap() - Generic panic message
    let value1 = result.unwrap(); // 42
    println!("Unwrapped: {}", value1);

    // expect() - Custom panic message
    let result2: Result<i32, &str> = Err("Something went wrong");
    let value2 = result2.expect("Failed to get value"); 
    // Panics: "Failed to get value: Something went wrong"
}
```

