### 🧠 When to Use Each

#### `.unwrap()` - Quick & Dirty
```rust
use std::fs;

fn quick_prototype() {
    let contents = fs::read_to_string("config.txt").unwrap();
    println!("Config: {}", contents);
    // Panics with: "called `Result::unwrap()` on an `Err` value: ...")
}
```

#### `.expect()` - Self-Documenting Panic
```rust
use std::fs;

fn better_error_context() {
    let contents = fs::read_to_string("config.txt")
        .expect("Failed to read config file");
    println!("Config: {}", contents);
    // Panics with: "Failed to read config file: ...")
}
```

